HEADWORD: Totem post
<hw>To"tem post</hw> }</mhw>.
<def>A pole or pillar, carved and painted with a series of totemic
symbols, set up before the house of certain Indian tribes of the
northwest coast of North America, esp. Indians of the Koluschan
stock.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

